window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b><i>Confronting my family’s nemesis wasn’t on my to-do list. Neither was falling for him.</i></b><br> <br> After my difficult divorce, I thought my life was over. But now, I’m happier and more successful than I could’ve ever imagined. My cosmetics business is thriving and I’m almost ready to get back out there and find Mr. Right. <i>Almost.</i><br> <br> When I hear that a therapy ranch on the Bayou is seeking an investor, I jump at the opportunity. I know only too well that spending time with animals is healing.</p> <p>When I visit the owners to ask for details, I find out I’m not the only one interested. Zachary LeBlanc is also there to make an offer. Why is that a problem? His family ruined <i>my</i> family’s reputation. He immediately tries to discredit me in front of the owners. Needless to say, I’m ready to give Zachary LeBlanc a piece of my mind.<br> <br> Days later, I spot Zachary in the French Quarter, at the edge of the Mississippi River. As I hurry over to give it to him good, the unthinkable happens and I fall into the river! I’m certain I’ll drown, but he somehow pulls me out. That’s when I see an entirely new side to this man — though maybe I’m still in shock from the trauma. Zachary is kind and patient, but before long, we’re back to arguing again.<br> And that’s when he kisses me! After he pulls back, I wonder if his intention was to shut me up, or if he’s truly attracted to me.</p> <p>One thing I know for sure; I've met my match in Zachary Leblanc. Because I'm not going down without a fight, and neither is he.</p> <p><b><i>There are so many reasons why we can’t be together. So why am I ignoring all of them?</i></b></p>"; 
